I think most if not all of the people rating this movie highly must be teenagers. This is pretty nasty hollywood garbage I barely managed to make it through. It's directed TERRIBLY. Slow mo shots of things which aren't interesting -- soaring scenes of epic macho bullshit alternating with insipid "grrl power" warmed over from the Winona & Angelina movie from a decade ago. Terrible acting. Top 40 pop hits in the background almost constantly, relegating the movie to little more than a glorified music video and making it clear this movie is for teens. Thoroughly tasteless & garish in ways only teens and hollywood-lovers would not notice. I think it wanted to come across a bit like Scott Pilgrim, blurring fantasy & real life, but Scott Pilgrim is far, far superior.
